{
  "info": {
    "name": "ASMS - Apartment Service Management System",
    "_postman_id": "asms-api-collection-v1",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the ASMS microservices platform.\n\n## Base URL\nSet the `baseUrl` variable to your ALB URL.\nDefault: `http://k8s-asmsprod-asmsingr-7dc3e4d184-282727532.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com`\n\n## Getting a Token\nRun **00 - Auth → Get Token** directly in Postman. Keycloak is exposed through the ALB at `/realms/*`.\n\nThe token is auto-saved to `{{token}}` by the test script — no kubectl needed.\n\nAvailable test users (all password `Test@1234`):\n- `testuser` — ADMIN\n- `rwa.member` — RWA_MEMBER\n- `resident` — OWNER\n- `security.guard` — SECURITY\n\n## Roles\n- `ADMIN` / `RWA_MEMBER` — management endpoints (list users, manage tickets, etc.)\n- `OWNER` / `TENANT` — resident actions (raise ticket, make payment, approve visitor)\n- `SECURITY` — log and control visitor entry\n- `SUPPORT_STAFF` — resolve support tickets\n- `VENDOR` — vendor operations\n\n## Enum Values\n**UserRole:** ADMIN, RWA_MEMBER, OWNER, TENANT, VENDOR, SECURITY, SUPPORT_STAFF\n**AmenityType:** SWIMMING_POOL, GYM, CLUBHOUSE, TENNIS_COURT, BADMINTON_COURT, BANQUET_HALL, LIBRARY, KIDS_PLAY_AREA, TERRACE, OTHER\n**TicketCategory:** PLUMBING, ELECTRICAL, CARPENTRY, HOUSEKEEPING, SECURITY, LIFT, WATER_SUPPLY, INTERNET, PARKING, COMMON_AREA, OTHER\n**TicketPriority:** P1_CRITICAL, P2_HIGH, P3_MEDIUM, P4_LOW\n**PaymentMethod:** UPI, CARD, NET_BANKING, WALLET, CASH\n**InvoiceType:** MONTHLY_MAINTENANCE, AMENITY_BOOKING, WATER_CHARGES, PARKING, PENALTY, AD_HOC\n**WorkflowType:** VENDOR_ONBOARDING, MAINTENANCE_REQUEST, LEASE_RENEWAL, CONSTRUCTION_PERMIT, FACILITY_BOOKING",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://k8s-asmsprod-asmsingr-7dc3e4d184-282727532.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "JWT Bearer token from Keycloak. Obtain via kubectl exec (see collection description)."
    },
    {
      "key": "societyId",
      "value": "SOCIETY-001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "userId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Create User response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "amenityId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Create Amenity response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "bookingId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Create Booking response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "ticketId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Create Ticket response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "visitorId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Log Visitor Entry response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "paymentId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Initiate Payment response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "invoiceId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Generate Invoice response script"
    },
    {
      "key": "workflowId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically by Submit Approval response script"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 - Auth",
      "description": "Keycloak token operations. Token must be obtained via kubectl exec since Keycloak is not exposed externally.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('Token saved. Expires in:', json.expires_in, 'seconds');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.error('No access_token in response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "client_id",  "value": "asms-client",    "type": "text" },
                { "key": "username",   "value": "testuser",        "type": "text" },
                { "key": "password",   "value": "Test@1234",       "type": "text" },
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "password",        "type": "text" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/realms/asms/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["realms", "asms", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Keycloak is exposed through the ALB at /realms/*.\n\nThe token is auto-saved to {{token}} by the test script.\n\nSwitch username to test different roles:\n- testuser / Test@1234  → ADMIN\n- rwa.member / Test@1234 → RWA_MEMBER\n- resident / Test@1234  → OWNER\n- security.guard / Test@1234 → SECURITY"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "01 - Users",
      "description": "User registration and management. POST (create) has no auth. All GET/PATCH/DELETE require a valid JWT.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (json.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', json.id);",
                  "    pm.test('User created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"John\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@asms.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"9876543210\",\n  \"role\": \"OWNER\",\n  \"societyId\": \"{{societyId}}\",\n  \"unitId\": \"A-101\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "users"]
            },
            "description": "No auth required. Valid roles: ADMIN, RWA_MEMBER, OWNER, TENANT, VENDOR, SECURITY, SUPPORT_STAFF"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get User by ID",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "users", "{{userId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Requires any authenticated role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Users",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?societyId={{societyId}}&page=0&size=20",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "users"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "societyId", "value": "{{societyId}}" },
                { "key": "role",   "value": "OWNER",   "disabled": true },
                { "key": "status", "value": "ACTIVE",  "disabled": true },
                { "key": "page",   "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size",   "value": "20" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Requires ADMIN or RWA_MEMBER role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update User",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"John\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Smith\",\n  \"phone\": \"9876543211\",\n  \"unitId\": \"A-102\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "users", "{{userId}}"]
            },
            "description": "ADMIN/RWA_MEMBER can update any user. A user can update themselves (id matches authentication.name)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete User",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "users", "{{userId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Requires ADMIN role. GDPR erasure — permanently removes user data."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
